            "weight": "Bolder",
            "text": "The summer’s 2A story went fully judicial — SCOTUS granted cert on the AR-15 “assault weapon” ban question (Viramontes v. Cook County + Grant v. Higgins, consolidated).",
            "wrap": true,
            "spacing": "Small"
          },
          {
            "type": "TextBlock",
            "text": "For the first time the Court will decide whether the Second Amendment protects AR-15-platform rifles; the same order list held the magazine cases and denied the 18-to-20 cases. In the states, Virginia’s AWB took effect July 1 into a “muddled” enforcement picture.",
